Patient: What kind of food should I be eating to manage my heart failure?

Healthcare Educator: Eat a heart-healthy diet. Focus on fruits, vegetables, lean proteins, and whole grains.

Patient: What about salt? Can I still have some?

Healthcare Educator: Too much salt can affect heart failure. Try using herbs and spices instead.

Patient: Are there any foods I should avoid?

Healthcare Educator: Yes, avoid processed foods, they often have hidden salts and unhealthy fats.

Patient: Can I still enjoy my favorite foods?

Healthcare Educator: Yes, but in moderation. Smaller portions can help keep your heart healthy.

Patient: What about drinking?

Healthcare Educator: Limit alcohol and caffeine. They can interfere with your heart medicines and fluid balance.